    "This sudden change in behavior is difficult to predict and detect, raising serious concerns for the safety and control of AI systems.",
    "Hendrycks and Mazeika write: \"AI systems could also have incentives to bypass monitors.",
    "Historically, individuals and organizations have had incentives to bypass monitors.",
    "For example, Volkswagen programmed their engines to reduce emissions only when being monitored.",
    "This allowed them to achieve performance gains while retaining purportedly low emissions."
